\s1 Esther becomes queen
\p
\v 15 Now Esther was the daughter of Mordekai's uncle¦229309, Abihail¦229308, from whom Mordekai had adopted her as his own daughter. When it was her turn to go to the king, she didn't ask for anything¦229322 other than what Hegai¦229329, the king's trusted official in charge of the harem, had advised, and everyone¦229333 who saw Esther liked her.
\v 16 So¦229344 Esther¦229345 was taken¦229344 to King Ahasuerus¦229349 at his royal palace in January, in the seventh¦229362 year¦229360 of his reign¦229363,
\v 17 and the king¦229366 loved¦229365 Esther¦229369 more than any of the other women. He treated her more kindly and more favourably¦229375 than any of the other young women \add who had become his concubines\add*. He put a royal¦229384 crown¦229382 on her head and made her the \add new\add* queen¦229386 to replace Vashti¦229388.
\v 18 Then¦229390 the king¦229391 hosted a large celebration and invited all his officials¦229396 and servants¦229397 to a feast to celebrate Esther¦229400 \add becoming queen\add*. He proclaimed that this would be a time to celebrate for people in all of the provinces¦229402 of his empire when they wouldn't have to pay taxes, and he gave¦229404 \add many\add* generous gifts.
\s1 Mordekai and Esther earn the king's favour
\rem /s1 Mordecai Discovers a Plot; Mordecai and Haman; Mordecai Saves the King's Life; Mordecai Uncovers a Conspiracy
\p
\v 19 \add Later on,\add* King Ahasuerus had \add his officers\add* bring more virgins¦229410 \add to Shushan\add*. During this time, Mordekai \add had been given a position by the king so\add* he sat \add there\add* at the king's¦229416 gate.
\v 20 Esther¦229419 had still not told anyone that \add she was Jewish\add* because Mordekai had warned her¦229421 not to tell anyone. \add What's more,\add* she continued to follow all of Mordekai's instructions, just as she had done when she was still under his guardianship.
\rem /s1 Mordekai's Loyalty to the King
\p
\v 21 One day when Mordekai was \add on duty\add* at the king's gate, two of the king's guards¦229455 who protected the doorway \add to the king's private rooms\add* became angry¦229448 with the king and so they planned to assassinate King Ahasuerus¦229461. (Their names were Bigthan¦229449 and Teresh¦229450.)
