\p
\v 1 When Mordekai found out about what had been done, he tore his clothes¦229874 and dressed in sackcloth¦229876 and \add threw\add* ashes¦229877 \add over himself (as a sign of mourning or distress)\add* and went¦229878 out into the city¦229880 centre, wailing loudly¦229883 and bitterly¦229884.
\v 2 But¦229886 no one was wearing mourning garb was allowed inside the king's gate, so when Mordekai reached the gate, he had to stay just outside it.
\v 3 In every province¦229904 of the empire, the letter that said to destroy the Jews was publicly displayed and when the Jews heard about it¦229921, they were incredibly upset. They skipped meals and wailed loudly, and many of them also wore sackcloth¦229919 and threw ashes¦229920 on themselves and lay on the ground.
\p
\v 4 When \add Queen\add* Esther's¦229929 young female attendants came¦229924 with her guardians and told her \add what was going on outside\add*, even the queen¦229934 became very scared. She sent¦229936 Mordekai some good clothes¦229938 to wear instead of the sackcloth¦229943, but he wouldn't accept¦229946 them.
