\p
\v 12 \add So¦230117 Hathak\add* went back to Mordekai and told him what the queen had said.
\v 13 Mordekai told \add Hathak\add* to tell this to Esther¦230129: “Don't imagine¦230132 that just because you live there in the king's palace that you'll be safe when they kill all the other Jews.
\v 14 If you say nothing at all now, someone from some other place¦230153 will rescue the Jews, but you and your relatives will not survive. Who knows, perhaps it was for a time just like this that \add God allowed\add* you to become queen?”
