\p
\v 4 “If it pleases your majesty,” Esther¦230302 replied, “please come¦230309 with Haman¦230311 today to the banquet¦230315 that I've prepared for you.”
\p
\v 5 The king said to his servants, “\add Go and\add* get Haman” the king told his servants, “and bring¦230323 him quickly¦230323 so that we can do what the queen has asked us.” So¦230321 the king and Haman went¦230332 to the banquet¦230337 that Esther¦230331 had had prepared for them.
\v 6 While they were drinking¦230346 wine, the king said to Esther¦230345, “Now please tell me what you \add really\add* want. I'll give you anything you ask for, no matter how much it is. I truly mean what I am saying.”
\p
\v 7 “This is what I \add really\add* want.” Esther¦230363 replied.
