\s1 Haman's anger with Mordekai and his execution plan
\rem /s1 Haman Plots to Kill Mordecai; Haman's Plan to Kill Mordecai; Haman Plans to Have Mordecai Hanged; Haman's Rage Against Mordecai
\p
\v 9 Haman was feeling very happy as he left \add the banquet\add* that day¦230404. But¦230402 then he saw¦230409 Mordekai sitting at the king's gate and noticed that Mordekai didn't stand up or show fearful reverence to him. This made Haman furious with Mordekai
\v 10 but he restrained himself and went¦230432 home¦230435. Then¦230430 he sent¦230436 for his friends¦230440 and brought¦230437 in his wife, Zeresh¦230443,
\v 11 boasting to them about how rich he was and about how many sons he had, and how the king had promoted¦230463 him \add many times\add* and given him a position above¦230464 all of the other officials¦230466 and administrators.
\v 12 “And that is not all,” Haman¦230471 added. “I was the only one that Queen Esther¦230476 invited to go with the king to a banquet¦230483 that she prepared¦230486 for us today. And she's also invited only me to go with the king again tomorrow¦230493.
\v 13 However, I still can't be happy as long as I keep seeing¦230513 that Jew, Mordekai, sitting¦230518 there at the king's¦230520 gate.”
